                        <p class="placename">
                L&#195;d Ghetto<br /><span class="alt">(Litzmannstadt Ghetto)</span>
            </p>
                                    <p class="municipality">
                <strong>Location:</strong>
                L&#195;d, Poland<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                Created on May 1, 1940 to intern the 164,000 original Jewish inhabitants of &#195;d, most of whom were killed at Chelmno or sent to labor camps. During the war, some 43,000 people died there from starvation and disease. When the Russian army occupied &#195;d in January 1945, only 877 Jews remained.
            </div>
