                <strong>Location:</strong>
                Czstochowa, Poland<br />
                            </p>
                            <div>
                Established in April 1941, it was largely liquidated in September-October 1942 and the survivors sent to the Treblinka concentration camp.  A &#34;Small Ghetto&#34; of around 5000 remained of the strongest and best-educated, but these were dispersed or liquidated as well by July 1943.
            </div>
